om/mistakes-ive-made-as-an-engineering-manager/\">Mistakes I've Made as an Engineering Manager</a> - Mistakes: “1) Thinking people give feedback the way they want to receive it; 2) Trying to do everything yourself; 3) Communicating something one time is enough; 4) You have to have everything together all the time.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:44:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cognitive Tools</h2><h3>Collections</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.foundingfuel.com/article/gigerenzers-simple-rules/\">Gigerenzer's simple rules</a> - The reason we often relies on these simple heuristics: “outside the lab, in real world, we cannot do well with just with logical rationality, we need ecological rationality - the kind of thinking that helps us get what we want in an environment that's uncertain and dynamic. This means exercising our instincts, using simple but robust rules of thumb.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:44:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Re-organizations</h2><h3>Company-level</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jessitron.com/2021/05/26/a-high-resilience-org-chart/\">A high-resilience org chart</a> - “If you know what problem you're solving and you know how to solve it, a bureaucratic organization will do. Stick with what you know. If you're writing software, that's a generative activity. You need a high-resilience org chart. Fewer boxes, more flexibility.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:44:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Recruitment</h2><h3>Interview</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://staysaasy.com/leadership/2021/04/12/the-intangible-skills-you-cant-interview-for.html\">The Intangible Skills You Can't Interview For</a> - “1) Cut-Through on Crappy Tasks; 2) Knowing How to Finish; 3) Knowing How to Start; 4) Giving (And Receiving) Diagonal Feedback; 5) Harnessing the Value of Intangibles.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:41:37.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-iam","categoryHTML":"<h2>Authentication</h2><h3>Multi-Factor</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://syslog.ravelin.com/2fa-is-missing-a-key-feature-c781c3861db\">2FA is missing a key feature</a> - “When my 2FA code is entered incorrectly I'd like to know about it”.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:40:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-falsehood","categoryHTML":"<h2>Networks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.netmeister.org/blog/urls.html\">URLs: It's complicated…</a> - There's a lot of components in an URL, and all have their own logic.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:37:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Consultants</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dabit3.medium.com/the-prosperous-software-consultant-5dc8d705c5dd\">The Prosperous Software Consultant</a> - This article let you understand how an independent consultant operates.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:30:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-iam","categoryHTML":"<h2>UX/UI</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://learnui.design/blog/tips-signup-login-ux.html\">11 Tips for Better Signup / Login UX</a> - Some basic tips on the login form.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:30:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://betterprogramming.pub/10-admirable-attributes-of-a-great-technical-lead-251d13a8843b\">10 Admirable Attributes of a Great Technical Lead</a> - “They are smart yet kind. Knowledgeable, yet humble. Busy, yet approachable.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:30:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Project Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://iism.org/article/developers-can-t-fix-bad-management-57\">Developers can't fix bad management</a> - “Why do so many software projects fail? Software development is much closer to creating a new factory than running an existing factory. (…) Software development is made up of many unknown duration tasks, this fundamentally unpredictable nature makes traditional management's predictive planning techniques particularly unsuited for software projects.”</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:30:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Finance</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.finops.org/introduction/what-is-finops/\">What is FinOps</a> - A framework for tech finance and business leadership teams to share the same language and processes of cloud operations and management.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:29:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-billing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Taxes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.streamlinedsalestax.org/about-us/about-sstgb\">Streamlined Sales Tax Governing Board</a> - A multi-states US initiative to automate and standadize sales tax accounting and collection.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-07-03T11:29:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"matteocrippa/awesome-swift","categoryHTML":"<h2>Patterns</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pointfreeco/swift-composable-architecture\">The Composable Architecture</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pointfreeco/swift-composable-architecture\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">7.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_ST